Here's my proposed API:

``` js
// rollup.config.js
export default {
  entry: 'src/index.js',
  plugins: [‚Ä¶],
  targets: [
    {
      format: 'umd',
      moduleName: 'thing',
      dest: 'dist/thing.js'
    },
    {
      format: 'es6',
      dest: 'dist/thing.mjs'
    }
  ]
};
```

This does not allow different plugins, entry, or any of the "input" options, so it may not work for you @tkissing. This would meet my needs, though. Perhaps we could allow all the options in the targets, but if you specified only differing output then rollup would only have to build the bundle once as an optimization?
